<AUs>Hyypia, Mirva|Parjanen, Satu</AUs>

<AUf>Hyypia, Mirva</AUf>

<TI>Boosting the Creativity and Communication in the Innovation Processes - Preliminary Results From the Qualitative Study</TI>

<TIss>boost||creativ||communic|||innov|process|preliminari|result|||qualit||</TIss>

<SO>PROCEEDINGS OF THE 5TH INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCE ON INTELLECTUAL CAPITAL|AND KNOWLEDGE MANAGEMENT & ORGANISATIONAL LEARNING</SO>

<LA>English</LA>

<DT>Proceedings Paper</DT>

<KWs>Knowledge sharing| proximity| distance| trust| transformational|leadership| managerial roles</KWs>

<KWss>knowledg shar|proxim|distanc|trust|transform|leadership|manageri rol|</KWss>

<DEs>PROXIMITY</DEs>

<DEss>proxim|</DEss>

<AB>The current business environment demands more suitable tools and practices for knowledge sharing between different groups in the organizations, as well as in the networks. In addition, leadership and managerial roles and practices require changes in order to meet the pressure of the surroundings. There is a significant impact on proximity between people and knowledge sharing. The proximity is seen as an important pre-condition for knowledge sharing and knowledge transfer. The different dimensions of proximity reduce uncertainty and solve the problem of coordination and facilitate interactive learning and innovation. But proximity may also negatively affect new ideas and innovations due to the problem of lock-in, meaning a lack of openness and flexibility.|It is argued that communities of practice are ideal for learning in an organization. Longstanding relationships and established practices reduce mistrust and enable learning. Lack of trust can prevent people from asking questions and sharing knowledge. This is usually true concerning learning in the sense of absorbing knowledge from others in the group. But when it concerns learning in the sense of innovation, the communities of practice might not always be ideal because of their rather small cognitive distance. If things are always done the same way it is not possible to think in new ways. Innovation often requires dissimilar, complementary bodies of knowledge. Cognitive diversity will increase the likelihood of creative new knowledge emerging. Therefore knowledge sharing between different communities in practice is essential. Through the interaction of diverse groups, it is possible to overcome the factors constraining the development of new knowledge.|With the proper combination of systems, practices and diverse individuals, organizations can create a motivated and trusted work environment. This study seeks to find how leadership and managerial roles influence creativity and innovation processes in an organization. In addition, the study recognizes those characteristics of leadership that affect the aspiration to share knowledge among different individuals and groups in the organization.</AB>

<ABss>|current|busi|environ|demand||suitabl|tool||practic||knowledg|share||differ|group|||organ||well||||network||addit|leadership||manageri|role||practic|requir|chang||order||||pressur|||surround||||signific|impact||proxim||peopl||knowledg|share||proxim|||||import|precondit||knowledg|share||knowledg|transfer||differ|dimens||proxim|reduc|uncertainti||solv||problem||coordin||facilit|interact|learn||innov||proxim|may||negat|affect|new|idea||innov||||problem||lockin|mean||lack||open||flexibility|it||argu||communiti||practic||ideal||learn|||organ|longstand|relationship||establish|practic|reduc|mistrust||enabl|learn|lack||trust||prevent|peopl||ask|question||share|knowledg|||usual|true||learn|||sens||absorb|knowledg||other|||group||||concern|learn|||sens||innov||communiti||practic|might||alway||ideal||||rather|small|cognit|distanc|if|thing||alway|done|||||||possibl||think||new||innov|often|requir|dissimilar|complementari|bodi||knowledg|cognit|divers|will|increas||likelihood||creativ|new|knowledg|emerg|therefor|knowledg|share||differ|communiti||practic||essenti|||interact||divers|group|||possibl||overcom||factor|constrain||develop||new|knowledge|with||proper|combin||system|practic||divers|individu|organ||creat||motiv||trust|work|environ|||seek||find||leadership||manageri|role|influenc|creativ||innov|process|||organ||addit|||recogn||characterist||leadership||affect||aspir||share|knowledg||differ|individu||group|||organ|</ABss>

<INs>Lappeenranta Univ Technol | </INs>

